	<div class="post post-96261 clearfix  category-uncategorized">
		<div class="slugs"><a title="magic" href="http://thehairpin.com/slug/magic-2">magic</a></div>
		<a class="comments" href="http://thehairpin.com/2015/02/what-is-the-natural-sound-of-your-voice#comments">0</a>

				<h2><a    title="What Is the Natural Sound of Your Voice?" href="http://thehairpin.com/2015/02/what-is-the-natural-sound-of-your-voice">What Is the Natural Sound of Your Voice?</a></h2>
		<div class="byline">
			<a title="Sulagna Misra" href="http://thehairpin.com/user/56517/sulagnamisra">Sulagna Misra</a>			<a class="time" href="http://thehairpin.com/2015/02/what-is-the-natural-sound-of-your-voice">| February 18, 2015</a>
		</div>
		
		<div class="entry clearfix">
			<p><a href="http://thehairpin.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Natural-Sound-of-Your-Voice-Hairpin.jpg"><img src="http://thehairpin.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Natural-Sound-of-Your-Voice-Hairpin-640x400.jpg" alt="sulagnaMADETHIS" width="640" height="400" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-96262" /></a></p>

<p><b>What’s your favorite light?</b><br />
1. Fragmented sunlight filtered through the leaves of trees.<br />
2. The flicker of your nightlight as you read one… more… page.<br />
3. Sunshine filling a room.<br />
4. The pallor of the moon silvering up the world.<br />
5. The high beams of incoming visitors.<br />
6. The sudden brightening of a screen.</p>

<p><B>Who do you see in your dreams? (Choose all that apply, add them together and find the average.)</b><br />
1. You speak comfortably with people you’ve seen in books, movies, magazines, but never in real life. Then someone who you do know in real life shows up and you stutter.<br />
2. You’re driving—a car, a plane, it doesn’t matter, but you’re moving forward, trying to catch that horizon.<br />
3. You sit quietly with a friend or relative you haven’t seen in a while. You discuss a book you read recently, or that movie everyone’s talking about.<br />
4. Grab the bag, there’s no time! Jump on the train, you must escape quickly. Hide from them, you know too mu—hey, it’s morning.<br />
5. You pull off your fingers and stick them on your feet. Then you turn into a circle.<br />
6. You walk through a giant grey house. You finally find a person. No, it’s a mirror. You look at it and smile. No, your teeth fall out. You turn around and face your betrayer.  <a class="more-link" title="Read More" href="http://thehairpin.com/2015/02/what-is-the-natural-sound-of-your-voice#more">READ MORE</a></p>		</div><!-- .entry -->
	</div><!-- .post -->














